occurrences.line_text: Thus fowle to hasten your vntimely date;
To finish it: that so vntimely breach
The eldest brother did vntimely dy;
Some for vntimely ease, some for delight,
Both leafe and fruit, both too vntimely shed,
Now is the time, that I vntimely must
Brought in vntimely houre, ere it was sought.
His name was Guizor, whose vntimely fate
Like fruitles seede, of which vntimely death should grow.
That with vntimely drought nigh withered was,
Vntimely dyde, before I did attaine
But false Duessa now vntitled Queene,
But forth vnto the darksome hole he went,
The stroke down fro[m]; her head vnto her shoulder glaunst.
Add faith vnto your force, and be not faint:
Halfe furious vnto his foe he came,
But still did follow one vnto the end,
Vnto their lodgings then his guestes he riddes:
And vnto Morpheus comes, whom drowned deepe
And threatned vnto him the dreaded name
In hast vnto his Lord, where he him left afore.
Vnto that Elfin knight he bad him fly,
Faire Venus seemde vnto his bed to bring
That for my sake vnknowne such griefe vnto you grew.
Vnto his guest, who after troublous sights
How he may worke vnto her further smarts:
Betrothed me vnto the onely haire
Which I do owe vnto all woman kind,
Yet wished tydings none of him vnto her brought.
Vnto this house he brought, and did bestow
Vnto an hill; from whence when she him spyde,
That should as death vnto my deare hart light:
When nigh he drew vnto this gentle payre
For vnto knight there is no greater shame,
And vnto hell him selfe for money sold;
His life was nigh vnto deaths doore yplast,
He led a wretched life vnto him selfe vnknowne.
The fowle Duessa, next vnto the chaire
She is ybrought vnto a paled greene,
And vnto battaill bad them selues addresse:
But comes vnto the place, where th'Hethen knight
Vnto the place, whereas the Paynim lay,
Till they be come vnto the furthest part:
But vnto hell did thrust him downe aliue,
Vnto his maister, he no lenger would
Vnto the place they come incontinent:
They drawing nigh, vnto their God present
And made her person thrall vnto his beastly kind.
And bore a boy vnto that saluage sire:
Vnto the woods, to see her little sonne;
Vnto those natiue woods for to repaire,
But she all vowd vnto the Redcrosse knight,
And me thy worthy meed vnto thy Leman take.
Vnto her natiue prison to retourne:
Then downe againe she fell vnto the ground;
The which these reliques sad present vnto mine eie.
She heard with patience all vnto the end,
And loue fresh coles vnto her fire did lay:
Vnto his foe, a Gyant huge and tall,
Vnto his aide she hastily did draw
Vnto the Gyant loudly she gan call,
And yields it selfe vnto the victours might;
Her golden cup she cast vnto the ground,
So brought vnto his Lord, as his deserued pray.
Whom these sad eyes saw nigh vnto deaths dore,
Forthwith he gaue in charge vnto his Squire,
At last he came vnto an yron doore,
Vnto old Timon he me brought byliue,
That I was sonne and heire vnto a king,
Of grace do me vnto his cabin guide.
To come vnto his wished home in haste,
And brought vnto him swords, ropes, poison, fire,
The Porter opened vnto them streight way:
She vnto him disclosed euery whit,
Eftsoones vnto an holy Hospitall,
And lodging, vnto all that came, and went:
Not vnto such, as could him feast againe,
Which as a stocke he left vnto his seede;
That from the first vnto the last degree,
From thence, far off he vnto him did shew
Her loftie towres vnto the starry sphere,
More deare vnto their God, then you[n]glings to their dam.
And shortly backe returne vnto this place,
Now are we come vnto my natiue soyle,
Vnto you bring, to ease you of your misery.
Such noyse his rouzed scales did send vnto the knight.
And three mens strength vnto the stroke he layd;
For vnto life the dead it could restore,
Like Eyas hauke vp mounts vnto the skies,
The hell-bred beast threw forth vnto the skyes,
Vnto the watchman on the castle wall;
Vnto that doughtie Conquerour they came,
And added grace vnto her excellence:
Vnto another loue, and to another land.
Vnwares me wrought vnto her wicked will,
Vnto his Farie Queene backe to returne:
For we be come vnto a quiet rode,
Of such, as vertues like mote vnto him allye.
So can he turne his earnest vnto game,
He that made loue vnto the eldest Dame,
And fiercely vnto battell sterne themselues prepar'd.
But ere they could proceede vnto the place,
Vnto that stead, their strife to vnderstond;
And of her plenty adde vnto their need:
Vnto the iourney which he had behight:
The bloudy-handed babe vnto her truth
And doest not vnto death thy selfe prepaire.
Till that they come vnto a forrest greene,
That vnto thee due worship I may rightly frame.
Vnto the bush her eye did suddein glaunce,
Vnto her happie mansion attaine:
Which vnto things of valorous pretence
That vnto knighthood workes much shame and woe;
And both her hands fast bound vnto a stake,
But vnto him she would impart the same:
One day vnto me came in friendly mood,
Eftsoones he came vnto th'appointed place,
As griefe and furie vnto me did bring;
But added flame vnto his former fire,
He made him stoup perforce vnto his knee,
Vnto an aged woman, poore and bare,
Vnto his brother, whom Cymochles men did call.
The little barke vnto the shore to draw,
The merry marriner vnto his word
And come vnto an Island, waste and voyd,
Vnto her boat againe, with which she cleft
Vnto the other side of that wide strond,
And bared all his head vnto the bone;
Does yeeld vnto his foe a pleasant victory.
At last he came vnto a gloomy glade,
That of my plenty poure out vnto all,
And vnto none my graces do enuye:
Vnto thy bounteous baytes, and pleasing charmes,
So euill thing to seeke vnto their ayd,
By whom they passing, spake vnto them nought.
Therefore his house is vnto his annext;
Till that they came vnto an yron dore,
The charge thereof vnto a couetous Spright
Vnto another rowme, whose dore forthright,
Thereby more louers vnto her to call;
And vnto all that liue in high degree,
The Palmer lent his eare vnto the noyce,
The charge, which God doth vnto me arret,
The care thereof my selfe vnto the end,
And vnto battell doe your selues addresse;
If not, leaue vnto me thy knights last patronage.
Vnto such blisse? sufficient were that hire
The watch, and lowd vnto the knights did call,
Vnto the castle gate they come againe,
Vnto the ground she cast her modest eye,
And likest is vnto that heauenly towre,
That boy them sought, and vnto him did lend.
Who now shall giue vnto me words and sound,
Equall vnto this haughtie enterprise?
And lift it selfe vnto the highest skies?
That well can witnesse yet vnto this day
Thus Brute this Realme vnto his rule subdewd,
His life, and long good fortune vnto finall fate.
Vnto the mightie streame him to betake,
Then his ambitious sonnes vnto them twaine
Who vnto him assembling forreine might,
Were vnto him reueald in vision,
Betrayd his contrey vnto forreine spoyle:
He is againe vnto his rule restord,
That gaue vnto vs all, what euer good we haue.
And vnto each a Bulwarke did arret,
Whiles his long legs nigh raught vnto the ground;
Vnto his Tygres taile, and shot at him apace.
And striues to mount vnto his natiue seat;
But trust vnto his strength and manhood meare,
And vnto better fortune doth her selfe prepaire.
The lumpish corse vnto the senselesse grownd;
So soone as he vnto her wombe did fall;
Vntill he came vnto a standing lake;
Vntill they nigh vnto that Gulfe arriue,
Bidding them nigher draw vnto the shore;
A solemne Meane vnto them measured,
Is sweet, and pleasing vnto liuing sense,
Till that he came vnto another gate,
To her delights, she vnto him bewrayd:
Their notes vnto the voyce attempred sweet;
Now soft, now loud, vnto the wind did call:
Their diuerse notes t'attune vnto his lay,
Let them returned be vnto their former state.
And antique praises vnto present persons fit.
A little leaue vnto a rusticke Muse
Vnto his Faerie Queene he might present:
In which the sword was seruant vnto right;
Vnto his reskew, and with earnest cry,
And soone compeld to hearken vnto peace:
So vnto wrong to yield my wrested right:
Shall doe vnto her seruice neuer to remoue.
And we your liege men faith vnto you plight.
Eftsoones them brought vnto their Ladies sight,
With which faire Britomart gaue light vnto the day.
Vnto her vew, and company vnsoght;
Them to betake vnto their kindly rest;
Vnto their bowres to guiden euery guest:
Tydings of one, that hath vnto me donne
And gaue vnto king Ryence for his gard,
For then some hope I might vnto me draw,
Of filthy lust, contrarie vnto kind:
Vnto the Church, their prayers to appeale,
Thou haue it lastly brought vnto her Excellence.
Vnto these Sprights, to bring to perfect end.
And coosen vnto king Ambrosius:
Therefore submit thy wayes vnto his will,
And brother vnto Cador Cornish king,
In auncient times vnto great Britainee,
With lighter hearts vnto their home retird;
Vnto thy selfe, and equall courage to thee take.
But him perforce vnto the ground it bore:
Vnto the gladsome port of her intent:
Great Neptune, I auow to hallow vnto thee.
And vnto battell did her selfe prepaire.
This warlike sonne vnto an earthly peare,
The sea vnto him voluntary brings,
To bring her sonne vnto his last decay.
They easily vnto her charet beare:
At last they came vnto a double way,
That Ladies loue vnto his Lord forlent,
And clombe vnto his steed. So forth he went,
Are wont to cleaue vnto the lowly clay,
And vnto them complained, how that he
What seruice may I do vnto thee meete,
To yield himselfe vnto the mighty ill:
Vnto the man, that of him tydings to her brings.
Shortly vnto the wastefull woods she came,
And vnto Psyche with great trust and care
What end vnto that fearefull Damozell,
Did natiue courage vnto him supply,
Which, chearefull signe did send vnto her sight,
Vnto the place, to which her hope did guyde,
Vnto your dwelling, ignorant and loth,
As vnto her to vtter his desire;
Vnto his reskew ran, and greedily him sped.
And meekely stoup vnto the victour strong:
So ran the Geauntesse vnto the fight;
She lightly vnto him adioyned side to syde;
And meant vnto her prison to haue brought,
I might do seruice vnto gentle Dames,
In hope vnto my pleasure to haue won;
And was return'd againe vnto his Dame,
Vnto her sonne, that lay in feeble state;
And now he strength gan adde vnto his will,
But Florimell with him vnto his bowre he bore.
To winne her liking vnto his delight:
And offred kingdomes vnto her in vew,
Her will to win vnto his wished end.
And offrest sacrifice vnto the dead:
That hath himselfe vnto such seruice sold,
Vnto their rest, and all the keyes conuayd
Vnto their maister, who in bed was layd,
And slacke attendaunce vnto straungers call.
And raught vnto her heeles; like sunny beames,
Vnto their wils, and one eyes watch escape;
Vnto those knights aduenturous, to tell
Of deeds of armes, which vnto them became,
Brought vnto balefull ruine, was by name
Them go to rest. So all vnto their bowres were brought.
And Peece, that vnto parley eare will giue,
Vnto your patience, ne be ill ypaid;
And with fowle force vnto his will did driue,
Ne priuie be vnto your treasures graue.
Ne stayd he, till he came vnto the place,
Till that he came vnto a rockie hill,
That death and life attonce vnto him giues.
And his forwandred steed vnto him got:
And stoutly came vnto the Castle gate;
And scoffing, thus vnto his mother sayd,
Next vnto him was Neptune pictured,
Vnto the Victor of the Gods this bee:
Great liking vnto many, but true loue to feowe.
Issewed forth, and went vnto the dore,
Vnto a brasen pillour, by the which she stands.
Dernely vnto her called to abstaine,
Restore vnto her health, and former state;
And perfect hole, prostrate she fell vnto the ground.
At last she came vnto the place, where late
Vnto a Castell, lodged there to bee,
Still in a knot, vnto her heeles downe traced,
And dayly more offensiue vnto each degree.
And sought to bring all things vnto decay;
And vnto all his creatures so benigne,
Vnto his last confusion to bring,
With that he put his spurres vnto his steed,
Vntrue to God, and vnto man vniust,
That by themselues vnto themselues is wrought,
Did priuily put coles vnto his secret fire.
And eke vnto her lookes a law she made,
But yet his sisters skill vnto him lent
Which she by art could vse vnto her will,
Vnto the third, that his may so be trebly wext.
But vnto them what destinie was assynd,
To draw their dayes vnto the vtmost date,
Lo faitour there thy meede vnto thee take,
Haue I thus long thy life vnto thee let:
That making way vnto his dearest life,
Vnto her rest in Plutoes griesly land,
Yet leaue vnto his sorrow did not yeeld,
And so gaue way vnto his fell intent:
Vnto her natiue home from mortall miserie.
By all that vnto them was deare, did them beseeke.
Vnto her Coch remounting, home did ride,
Vnto the place of turneyment they came;
Vnto whose rescue forth rode Paridell;
Vnto the noble Knights of Maidenhead,
The third dayes prize vnto that straunger Knight,
Then first Cambello brought vnto their view
Next did Sir Triamond vnto their sight
Then did Sir Ferramont vnto them shew
Vnto the vulgar for good gold insted,
Vnto the second best, that lou'd her better;
Tho vnto Satyran she was adiudged,
That she vnto their portion might befall.
Whom, when he was vnto her selfe most nie,
Full busily vnto his worke ybent;
Ne let his speeches come vnto their eare.
Vnto his lofty steede he clombe anone,
Ah gentle Scudamour, vnto your grace
Shame and dishonour hath vnto me donne;
Vnto her sword and shield her soone betooke;
And yeeld vnto her weapon way to pas:
Shew'd all his bodie bare vnto the cruell dent.
To graunt vnto those warriours truce a whyle;
Ne henceforth be rebellious vnto loue,
I can not vnto you aread a right.
Then she, ne vnto whom I more true loue did beare.
Vnto some resting place, which mote befall,
Where goodly solace was vnto them made,
Vnto the loue of noble Britomart,
Continuall siege vnto her gentle hart;
That at the length vnto a bay he brought her,
And vnto her his congee came to take.
He vnto her would speedily reuert:
Vnto his caue farre from all peoples hearing,
Daughter vnto a Lord of high degree;
Vnto my choise by no meanes would assent,
So on a day vnweeting vnto wight,
Gan dight him selfe vnto his wonted sinne;
But for aduantage ground vnto him gaue,
That ere vnto his hellish den he raught,
Vnto those woods he turned backe againe,
And vnto euery thing did aunswere mum:
And euer when the Prince vnto him spake,
And humble homage did vnto him make,
Vnto his wonne, and with her mournefull muse
In th'end she her vnto that place did guide,
Eftsoones she flew vnto his fearelesse hand,
Onely few ruefull lookes vnto her sent,
Of tydings, what did vnto him betide,
Of Amoret, so neare vnto decay,
Her wounds, that vnto strength restor'd her soone anew.
And vnto rest themselues all onely lent,
And each vnto his lust did make a lawe,
Vnto abuse of lawlesse lust was lent,
And did themselues vnto their iourney dight.
That vnto death had doen him vnredrest,
And heauie sway, that hard vnto his crowne
Vnto the earth, and lay long while in senselesse swowne.
Vnto his bay, and captiued her thought.
Was spoyle to make, and wast them vnto nought,
Him wretched thrall vnto his dongeon brought,
Vnto the prison in her ioyous glee,
He though affide vnto a former loue,
Whereof when tydings came vnto mine eare,
To come forthwith vnto his Ladies bowre.
The deare affection vnto kindred sweet,
To open vnto him the prison dore,
And vnto former liberty restore.
And Placidas, they both vnto him ran,
And vnto Ladies loue would lend no leasure:
Vnto this houre, this present lucklesse howre,
And all those daungers vnto them declar'd,
Vnto whose trust the charge thereof was lent:
Yet much disdaining vnto him to lout,
He gan forthwith t'auale, and way vnto me yield.
The which did seeme vnto my simple doome,
Vnto that purposd place I did me draw,
Vnto the porch approcht, which open stood;
She wore much like vnto a Danisk hood
And vnto Venus grace the gate doth open right.
Besought her to graunt ease vnto my smart,
Yet vnto her obayed all the best.
That vnto euery person knew her part;
That vnto Venus seruices was sold.
Who playing on his harpe, vnto him drew
Of his owne fish vnto their festiuall,
Which the proud Humber vnto them had donne,
Vnto her waste, with flowres bescattered,
Vnto an other Canto I will ouerpas.
That seem'd vnlike vnto his earthly home:
There vnto him betid a disauentrous case.
I will them tell though vnto no man neare:
For heauen that vnto all lends equall eare,
Let then this plaint vnto his eares be borne,
Vnto the passion, that her heart opprest,
But if that life ye vnto me decree,
The which the prisoner points vnto the free,
And though vnto his will she giuen were,
So backe he came vnto her patient;
Vnto himselfe she came, and him besought,
Vnto the shinie heauen in haste she hide,
Which when he had vnto his mother told,
Nor vnto any meaner to complaine,
But vnto great king Neptune selfe did goe,
Made humble suit vnto his Maiestie,
But vnto her deliuered Florimell.
She gaue vnto him, gotten by her slight
And why? doe it declare vnto me trew.
Vnto the place he came within a while,
And streight him selfe vnto the fight addrest,
That done, vnto the Castle he did wend,
Vnto the battilment to be vpbrought,
Which done, vnto his former iourney he retourned.
And all things would reduce vnto equality.
And cluster thicke vnto his leasings vaine,
In sdeignfull wize he drew vnto him neare,
And thus vnto him spake, without regard or feare;
These towring rocks, which reach vnto the skie,
Is with the tide vnto an other brought:
Approching nigh vnto him cheeke by cheeke,
By Marinell, was vnto him affide,
But second vnto none in prowesse prayse;
To greet his guerdon vnto euery knight,
So vnto him they did addeeme the prise
And vnto all himselfe there open shewed,
Which didst that seruice vnto Florimell.
Or shew the wounds, which vnto thee befell;
Ne he his mouth would open vnto wight,
Vntill that Guyon selfe vnto him spake,
That vnto him the horse belong'd, and sayd;
True Iustice vnto people to diuide,
And throwne it vp vnto my brothers share:
Or God or Fortune vnto me did throw,
Vnto your selfe, said they, we giue our word,
Vnto your part, and pluckt from his away,
That what the sea vnto you sent, your own should seeme.
But that the sea hath it vnto me throwne?
That what the sea vnto you sent, your own should seeme.
And him restoring vnto liuing light,
So brought vnto his Lord, where he did sit,
As for to lead your selfe vnto your owne decay?
To attribute their folly vnto fate,
And vnto them wrought all the villany,
For ought or nought be wonne vnto her will,
Vnto the dwelling of that Amazone.
And gathering them vnto her citties gate,
Goe thou vnto that stranger Faery Knight,
Vnto those warlike Knights she warning sent.
Vnto the wall his way did fearelesse take,
Their sound did reach vnto the heauens hight.
And thenceforth vnto daunger opened way.
And like a greedie Beare vnto her pray,
Vnto the crooke t'abide the balefull stowre,
Vnto her selfe in secret she did call
Bound vnto me, but not with such hard bands
And all thy forces gather vnto thee;
Both worthie is for to be sewd vnto,
Vnto the prison, where her hart did thrall remaine.
Vnto her Queene, his freedome to haue gayned;
Therefore vnto her mistresse most vnkind
To beare vnto her loue the message of her mind.
She vnto Talus forth return'd againe,
Me to deceiue of faith vnto me plight,
Was glad to yeeld vnto his good request:
Then Britomart vnto a bowre was brought;
Vnto your losse: and now needes will ye sleepe?
With that there came vnto her chamber dore
Gan her addresse vnto her former way.
Who as she nigh vnto them drew, the one
These vile reproches gan vnto her speake;
But putting spurres vnto her fiery beast,
And altars vnto him, and temples lent,
Vnto whose temple when as Britomart
Thence forth vnto the Idoll they her brought,
Vnto her selfe her silent prayers did impart.
There did appeare vnto her heauenly spright
All which when he vnto the end had heard,
All which when she vnto the end had heard,
Vnto the land of Amazons, as she was bent.
Vnto the man, whom thou doest loue so deare;
Vnto the bone, and made a griesly wound,
And pressing through the preace vnto the gate,
Gaue vnto her great comfort and reliefe,
Which he vnto her people does each day,
From her, vnto the miscreant him selfe,
So me in message vnto her she sent,
Vnto the Souldans court, her to present
Vnto his scornefull Lady, that for her had sent.
Vnto his horses gaue his guests for meat,
Gaue way vnto his horses speedie flying,
Oft drew the Prince vnto his charret nigh,
Still when he sought t'approch vnto him ny,
Yet could the Prince not nigh vnto him goe,
That one sure stroke he might vnto him reach,
And backe with both his hands vnto him hayles
But gathered vnto her her troubled wit,
Vnto the wyld wood ranne, her dolours to deplore.
Vnto that Damzell in her Ladies right,
